Monthly its $22 (sometimes more if I pick up a 3rd account of a friend for some reason, like KEI)<br>
Bought each part seperately, so thats 5*$40 or so, up to $200 there in sunk costs, then basically bought another computer and upgraded another with ned video card twice (another $2000 or so there, course I might of spent that anyway).  Throw in the extra phone line I had for a 3 years just to play at $25 ($150).  I guess that is about $3500 since it came out.  Have at least 260 played days (not including concurrent days hydraing).  Thats 6240 hours playing over the last 3 years or so?  Kind of depressing.  <br>
Course also did a lot of real life living and accomplishments at the same time.  Really its not bad for a hobby.  No DUI, no messing around on my wife, no broken bones or other injuries (maybe a little wrist soreness and probably dropped a little on the eyesight), but I look around at other people and what they blow money on, what they waste time on, and I don't think its too bad.  True, I won't be winning a nobel prize for my volunteer work in a third world country, but I don't know anyone that will either.  <br>
Have to be balanced, and while the scales tilt a little too far in the EQ direction, I enjoyed wasting all the time and money.<br>
